Sentencas: The effect of the Co doping on the structure, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-delta was investigated.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Co doping decreased the sintering temperature by about 100 degrees C and cubic structure was synthesized for Sr0.8Ce0.2Mn0.8Co0.2O3-delta.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of Sr0.8Ce0.2Mn0.8Co0.2O3-delta reached 102 S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C, which was sufficient to provide low ohmic losses at the cathode.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In comparison with Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-delta, the area-specific resistance of Sr0.8Ce0.2Mn0.8Co0.2O3-delta was 0.10 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C, which was about 20 times lower than that of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-delta.
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: While the exchange current density i(0) of Sr0.8Ce0.2Mn0.8Co0.2O3-delta was 0.49 A cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, that for Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-delta was 0.11 A cm(-2).
Titulo: Effect of Co doping on the properties of Sr0.8Ce0.2MnO3-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the Sr0.8Ce0.2Mn0.8Co0.2O3-delta cathode had high catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction in the temperature range of 700-800 degrees C. Crown Copyright (C) 2008 Published by Elsevier Ltd on behalf of International Association for Hydrogen Energy.
